  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge script CounterScript\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`getNonce` loads but doesn't touch the account leading to the failure of the following test\r\n\r\n```\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: UNLICENSED\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.13;\r\n\r\nimport \"../lib/forge-std/src/Script.sol\";\r\nimport \"../src/Counter.sol\";\r\n\r\ncontract CounterScript is Script {\r\n    uint256 fork1;\r\n    uint256 fork2;\r\n\r\n    function setUp() public {\r\n        fork1 = vm.createFork(\r\n            \"https://goerli.infura.io/v3/9aa3d95b3bc440fa88ea12eaa4456161\",\r\n            7475589\r\n        );\r\n        fork2 = vm.createFork(\r\n            \"https://api.avax-test.network/ext/bc/C/rpc\",\r\n            12880747\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    function run() public {\r\n        address user = address(0xF0959944122fb1ed4CfaBA645eA06EED30427BAA);\r\n\r\n        console.log(vm.getNonce(user)); // loaded but not touched\r\n\r\n        vm.selectFork(fork2);\r\n        assert(vm.getNonce(user) == 3); // fails here since the account was persisted\r\n        vm.prank(user);\r\n        new Counter();\r\n\r\n        vm.selectFork(fork1);\r\n        assert(vm.getNonce(user) == 3);\r\n        vm.prank(user);\r\n        new Counter();\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
